The paper deals with algorithms for computing minimal models, stable models, and answer sets, which are concepts related to artificial intelligence and logic programming. Therefore, cs.AI and cs.PL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the analysis of worst-case performance bounds, which is related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper deals with propositional logic, which falls under the sub-category of mathematical logic (cs.LO).
